@startuml
title Viewport and Clipping - Practical Flow

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

participant "Window" as Window
participant "Root Widget" as Root
participant "Child Widget" as Child
participant "RenderSnapshotBuilder" as SnapshotBuilder
participant "RenderCommand" as Command
participant "GPU" as GPU

Window -> Root : prepare root viewport from frame size
Root -> Child : provide parent viewport
Child -> Child : intersect geometry with parent viewport

Root -> SnapshotBuilder : append viewport command
Root -> SnapshotBuilder : append drawing commands
Child -> SnapshotBuilder : append clipped viewport
Child -> SnapshotBuilder : append child drawing commands

SnapshotBuilder -> Command : build snapshot commands
Command -> GPU : set viewport/scissor
Command -> GPU : draw only visible pixels

note bottom
Widget geometry limits where child widgets can draw.
The render path turns that visible area into viewport
and clipping commands.
end note

@enduml
